  "dimension_notes": {
    "error_consistency": {
      "evidence": [
        "Event publish failures are handled inconsistently in the same workflow area: `shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go` default emitter logs publish errors, while `withDefaultsWorkflowRuntime` drops them via `_ = eventRuntime.PublishUrbitTransition(...)`.",
        "`shipworkflow/newship.go` and `shipworkflow/newship_service.go` call `PublishNewShipTransition(...)` repeatedly without checking returned errors, despite `docker/events/events.go` defining explicit publish failure errors (`ErrTransitionBusFull`, `ErrTransitionPublishTimeout`).",
        "Several operational paths only log critical failures and continue toward success-like returns: `shipworkflow/newship.go` logs delete/stop/restart failures but continues provisioning; `shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go` logs stop failures in `urbitCleanDelete` then proceeds."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": ""
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "transition_publish_error_contract_drift",
      "summary": "Transition publish failures are ignored in some paths and surfaced in others",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/newship.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/newship_service.go",
        "goseg/docker/events/events.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`docker/events/events.go` publish APIs return concrete errors for timeout/full bus/not defined.",
        "`operations_runtime.go` has two contradictory strategies: one emitter logs `PublishUrbitTransition` failure, another path uses `_ = eventRuntime.PublishUrbitTransition(...)` and discards the error.",
        "`newship.go` and `newship_service.go` publish multiple new-ship transitions without checking return values, making dropped transition events invisible to callers."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define one explicit contract for transition publish failures (e.g., best-effort with throttled warning, or propagation for required transitions) and enforce it via a shared helper used by `operations_runtime.go`, `newship.go`, and `newship_service.go` so all publish calls handle errors consistently.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "implicit_best_effort_error_policy"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "async_task_errors_dropped_at_launch",
      "summary": "Fire-and-forget goroutines discard errors from functions that can fail",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/main.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/newship_service.go",
        "goseg/config/config_events.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`main.go` starts `http.ListenAndServe(\"0.0.0.0:6060\", nil)` in a goroutine without checking error.",
        "`newship_service.go` starts `go ProvisionShip(...)` although `ProvisionShip` returns `error`; the result is never observed.",
        "`config/config_events.go` legacy entrypoint `ConfChannel()` discards `StartConfEventLoop` error via `_ = ...`."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Use a consistent async error strategy: either route goroutine failures to an error channel/supervisor or explicitly wrap them in a helper that logs and classifies errors uniformly; avoid launching functions that return `error` without consuming their result.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "implicit_best_effort_error_policy"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "critical_operation_failures_logged_not_returned",
      "summary": "Critical cleanup/infra errors are logged and then treated as non-fatal inconsistently",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/shipworkflow/newship.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "In `ProvisionShip` (`newship.go`), container delete/volume delete/llama stop-start errors are logged but execution continues, mixing hard-fail and soft-fail behavior in one flow without a declared policy.",
        "In `urbitCleanDelete` (`operations_runtime.go`), `BarExitFn` and fallback stop failures are logged, then the function proceeds to delete, so callers cannot distinguish fully clean shutdown from partial failure."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Classify operations into required vs best-effort steps and encode that in return behavior (e.g., aggregate soft failures with `errors.Join` and return alongside main result, or expose a structured result with warnings) so callers get predictable failure semantics.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "implicit_best_effort_error_policy"
    }
  ],
